{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/SICP/Data-Abstraction/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"In Progress","author":"Kyeongin","siteUrl":"http://kkyeongin.github.io","comment":{"disqusShortName":"kkyeongin.github.io","utterances":"kkyeongin/kkyeongin.github.io"},"sponsor":{"buyMeACoffeeId":"QRsTu4dlJ"}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"6df40cbb-1677-5de4-8fd9-c094bb7d66b8","excerpt":"Data Abstraction 데이터의 구조를 숨기고 interface를 통해 사용\ndata를 combination하는 법을 알아보자. 들어가기 전에 procedural abstraction을 먼저 알아보자. procedural abstraction common pattern을 찾고 람다를 사용해서 procedure를 나타내고 이름을 붙인다. e.i 다시 사용될 코드는 밖에로 빼고\ndependency가 강한 것들은 같은 함수로 넣어주는 것이 좋다. \n—> block structure…","html":"<h1 id=\"data-abstraction\"><a href=\"#data-abstraction\" aria-label=\"data abstraction permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Data Abstraction</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>데이터의 구조를 숨기고 interface를 통해 사용\ndata를 combination하는 법을 알아보자.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>들어가기 전에 procedural abstraction을 먼저 알아보자.</p>\n<h2 id=\"procedural-abstraction\"><a href=\"#procedural-abstraction\" aria-label=\"procedural abstraction permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>procedural abstraction</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>common pattern을 찾고</li>\n<li>람다를 사용해서 procedure를 나타내고</li>\n<li>이름을 붙인다.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"ei\"><a href=\"#ei\" aria-label=\"ei permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>e.i</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"fs\"><pre class=\"language-fs\"><code class=\"language-fs\">let goodEnough guess x =\n    abs (guess * guess - x) &lt; 0.00001\n\nlet average x y =\n    (x+y) / 2.0\n\nlet improve guess x =\n    average guess (x / guess)\n\nlet rec loop guess x =\n    if goodEnough guess x\n    then guess\n    else loop (improve guess x) x\n    ; with full thinking\n\nlet sqrt x = loop 1.0 x</code></pre></div>\n<p>다시 사용될 코드는 밖에로 빼고\ndependency가 강한 것들은 같은 함수로 넣어주는 것이 좋다.\n—> block structure</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"block structure\"\n        title=\"block structure\"\n        src=\"/static/b7bee163eac671cb693dc07d66821790/b9e4f/block_structure.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b7bee163eac671cb693dc07d66821790/cf440/block_structure.png 148w,\n/static/b7bee163eac671cb693dc07d66821790/d2d38/block_structure.png 295w,\n/static/b7bee163eac671cb693dc07d66821790/b9e4f/block_structure.png 590w,\n/static/b7bee163eac671cb693dc07d66821790/164b6/block_structure.png 780w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"fs\"><pre class=\"language-fs\"><code class=\"language-fs\">let average x y =\n    (x+y) / 2.0\n\n; block structure\nlet sqrt x =\n    let goodEnough guess x =\n        abs (guess * guess - x) &lt; 0.00001\n    let improve guess x =\n        average guess (x / guess)\n    let rec loop guess x =\n        if goodEnough guess x\n        then guess\n        else loop (improve guess x) x\n    loop 1.0 x</code></pre></div>\n<p>이제 다시 돌아와서 Data Abstraction을 어떻게 이루어지 알아보자.  </p>\n<h2 id=\"compound-data\"><a href=\"#compound-data\" aria-label=\"compound data permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>compound data</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>묶어서 만들어야(constructor) 하며, 해체(selector or accessor) 또한 가능해야 한다.\npredicate; pair인지 아닌지 (boolean)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"pair\"><a href=\"#pair\" aria-label=\"pair permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>pair</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"fs\"><pre class=\"language-fs\"><code class=\"language-fs\">type Pair&lt;&#39;a,&#39;b&gt; = Pair of &#39;a * &#39;b\n\nlet cons x y = Pair (x,y)\nlet car (Pair (x,y)) = x\nlet cdr (Pair (x,y)) = y\n\nlet makePoint x y = cons x y\nlet pointX p = car p\nlet pointY p = cdr p\nlet makeLine p1 p2 = cons p1 p2\nlet start_point line = car line\n\n(*\nlengthOfLine = sqrt ((x1-x2)^2 + (y1 - y2)^2)\n*)</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"list\"><a href=\"#list\" aria-label=\"list permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>list</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.080213903743314%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"list 2\"\n        title=\"list 2\"\n        src=\"/static/91a3c28ca1f2f70f9f31b4b3c12d443e/b9e4f/list_2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/91a3c28ca1f2f70f9f31b4b3c12d443e/cf440/list_2.png 148w,\n/static/91a3c28ca1f2f70f9f31b4b3c12d443e/d2d38/list_2.png 295w,\n/static/91a3c28ca1f2f70f9f31b4b3c12d443e/b9e4f/list_2.png 590w,\n/static/91a3c28ca1f2f70f9f31b4b3c12d443e/30cfa/list_2.png 748w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>pair로 list를 만들 수도 있다. 구조체를 보자면 linked list다.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"fs\"><pre class=\"language-fs\"><code class=\"language-fs\">(*\nfromTo 1 4\n...\n==&gt; 1 :: (2 :: (3 :: (4 :: [])))\n...\n==&gt; [1;2;3;4]\n*)\n\nlet rec fromTo start finish =\n    if start &gt; finish then []\n    else start :: fromTo (start+1) finish</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"fs\"><pre class=\"language-fs\"><code class=\"language-fs\">let rec length ls =\n    if ls = [] then 0\n    else 1 + length (List.tail ls)</code></pre></div>\n<p>결론적으로 data abstructure는 data 구조가 어떻게 구현되었는지는 감춘다. constructor와 selector를 interface 통해 사용하면 된다.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 76.8545994065282%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"data abstraction\"\n        title=\"data abstraction\"\n        src=\"/static/8c5a26890de3e40d2e7b5adc7949e876/b9e4f/data_abstraction.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8c5a26890de3e40d2e7b5adc7949e876/cf440/data_abstraction.png 148w,\n/static/8c5a26890de3e40d2e7b5adc7949e876/d2d38/data_abstraction.png 295w,\n/static/8c5a26890de3e40d2e7b5adc7949e876/b9e4f/data_abstraction.png 590w,\n/static/8c5a26890de3e40d2e7b5adc7949e876/61857/data_abstraction.png 674w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>detail을 숨기고 interface를 사용하도록 한다면 나중의 확장성 및 변경에 영향이 없도록 함이다.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>관련 문서</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/electrical-engineering-and-computer-science/6-001-structure-and-interpretation-of-computer-programs-spring-2005/lecture-notes/lecture5webhand.pdf\">SICP<em>L5</em>Data Abstraction</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Data Abstraction","date":"February 20, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/SICP/Data-Abstraction/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/SICP/Type-1/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Type(1)","category":"SCIP"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/SICP/Symbol/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Symbol","category":"SCIP"}}}}}